So, heere's Peticioners attendance right; good words,
and ſhort commons: But tis not their entertainement wee come
for. I made a ſimple ſhift to get entertainement into the Court,

I ſhould ha more ground then halfe the Kinges in Chriſtendom:
here's my hand, Ile do't: my M. is my M. & I loue him;
but my gold's my God, and I honor it: Ile do't; the time & place?

I know not what shee is for a woman; marie I feare she's
litle better then a Whore for your Husband: harke in your eare;
shee's Manaſses wife.
